any defect in the Goods or Services;
any infringement or alleged infringement of any third-party Intellectual Property Right; and
any breach by Supplier of any applicable law or regulation.", "new_text": "10.1 INDEMNIFICATION BY SUPPLIER. Supplier shall indemnify, defend and hold harmless Buyer, its Affiliates, and their respective officers, directors, employees and agents from and against any and all claims, losses, damages, liabilities, costs and expenses (including reasonable legal fees on a full indemnity basis) arising out of or in connection with any breach by Supplier of this Agreement, any defect in the Goods or Services, any infringement or alleged infringement of any third-party Intellectual Property Right, or any breach by Supplier of any applicable law or regulation.

10.2 INDEMNIFICATION BY BUYER. Buyer shall indemnify, defend and hold harmless Supplier, its Affiliates, and their respective officers, directors, employees and agents from and against any and all claims, losses, damages, liabilities, costs and expenses (including reasonable legal fees on a full indemnity basis) arising out of or in connection with any breach by Buyer of this Agreement or any negligent act or omission of Buyer or its personnel.", "comment": "Makes indemnity mutual; removes uncapped 'any negligent act' trigger from Supplier; adds reciprocal obligation"}, {"type": "modify", "target_text": "10.2 The indemnities in this clause 10 are uncapped and survive termination.", "new_text": "10.3 CAP ON INDEMNITIES. Notwithstanding clauses 10.1 and 10.2, the aggregate liability of each Party under its indemnity obligations in this clause 10 shall not exceed the aggregate fees paid or payable by Buyer to Supplier in the twelve (12) months preceding the event giving rise to the claim. The indemnities in this clause 10 survive termination of this Agreement.", "comment": "Caps indemnities at 12-month fee cap, matching liability cap in clause 11"}, {"type": "modify", "target_text": "11.1 Subject always to clause 10 (which is uncapped), Supplier's aggregate liability under or in connection with this Agreement and any Order, whether in contract, tort (including negligence), misrepresentation or otherwise, shall not exceed an amount equal to the fees paid or payable by Buyer to Supplier in the twelve (12) months preceding the event giving rise to the claim.", "new_text": "11.1 Subject always to clause 10 (indemnities), the aggregate liability of each Party under or in connection with this Agreement and any Order, whether in contract, tort (including negligence), misrepresentation or otherwise, shall not exceed an amount equal to the fees paid or payable by Buyer to Supplier in the twelve (12) months preceding the event giving rise to the claim.", "comment": "Applies 12-month cap symmetrically to both Parties"}, {"type": "modify", "target_text": "11.2 Buyer's aggregate liability under or in connection with this Agreement, howsoever arising, shall in no event exceed £100,000.", "new_text": "11.2 DELETED. [See clause 11.1 — liability caps are reciprocal.]", "comment": "Removes asymmetric £100k Buyer cap; replaces with 12-month reciprocal cap"}, {"type": "modify", "target_text": "9.2 All Foreground IP — including any modifications, improvements, derivatives, or jointly developed materials arising in connection with this Agreement — shall vest in Buyer absolutely on creation. Supplier hereby assigns to Buyer with full title guarantee all such Foreground IP, including future rights.", "new_text": "9.2 JOINT OWNERSHIP OF FOREGROUND IP. All Foreground IP created jointly by the Parties shall be owned jointly by both Parties, with each Party having an equal undivided interest and the right to use such Foreground IP without obligation to the other. Foreground IP created solely by Supplier shall remain owned by Supplier, and Supplier grants Buyer a perpetual, irrevocable, royalty-free, worldwide, sublicensable licence to use such Foreground IP solely created by Supplier to the extent embedded in or required to exploit any Goods supplied under this Agreement.", "comment": "Changes from fullBuyer vesting to joint ownership; preserves Supplier background IP; adds licence for sole-created FG IP"}, {"type": "modify", "target_text": "18.1 Termination for Convenience. Buyer may terminate this Agreement or any Order at any time without cause on thirty (30) days' written notice to Supplier. No early-termination charges shall be payable other than reimbursement of demonstrable direct costs reasonably incurred up to the date of termination, capped at five percent (5%) of the value of work-in-progress on the termination date.", "new_text": "18.1 TERMINATION FOR CONVENIENCE.

(a) Buyer may terminate this Agreement or any Order without cause on thirty (30) days' written notice to Supplier, subject to reimbursement of demonstrable direct costs reasonably incurred up to the date of termination, capped at fifteen percent (15%) of the value of work-in-progress.

(b) In consideration of Supplier's commitments under this Agreement, Buyer undertakes to use its reasonable endeavours to place Orders totalling not less than [INSERT MINIMUM VOLUME: £40,000,000] across the Term, representing indicative annual spend of approximately £13.3m per annum. For the avoidance of doubt, 'reasonable endeavours' means placing Orders in accordance with Buyer's historical ordering patterns for MRO supplies and not diverting material spend to alternative suppliers without just cause.", "comment": "Increases early-termination compensation to 15%; adds minimum volume commitment"}, {"type": "modify", "target_text": "20.1 Order of precedence. In the event of any conflict between (a) this Agreement, (b) the GTCs, (c) the SLA, (d) the Compliance Annex, or (e) any Order, the order of precedence shall be (b), (a), (d), (c), (e). For the avoidance of doubt, the GTCs prevail over this Agreement.", "new_text": "20.1 ORDER OF PRECEDENCE. In the event of any conflict between (a) this Agreement, (b) the GTCs, (c) the SLA, (d) the Compliance Annex, or (e) any Order, the order of precedence shall be (a), (b), (d), (c), (e). For the avoidance of doubt, this Agreement (including clauses 9, 10, and 11 as marked up by Supplier) shall prevail over the GTCs. The Seller shall not rely on any amended GTCs introduced after the Effective Date to vary the terms agreed in this redlined Agreement.", "comment": "Reverses precedence so MSA prevails over GTCs; locks in agreed redline terms; prohibits post-contract GTCs amendment from overriding"}]

